@@eShadowmere -- As Kowloon Sees It@@N

@@gJade Magistracy, Emergency Powers Doctrine Review@@N

Shadowmere is the ruin of a @@ystate project@@N -- a frontier march
founded to extend Midgaard's law into unstable territory. Its horror
comes from @@rpolicy choices that outlived their emergency context@@N.
The Jade Magistracy studies it the way a navigator studies a wreck:
not for tragedy, but for the @@ycourse error@@N.

Kowloon knows this story because we almost @@rlived it@@N.

During the @@rAshfall Monsoon@@N, the surviving houses invoked emergency
powers. Water rationed by decree. Movement restricted. Gates sealed
without appeal. For three years, crisis authority ruled with no sunset
clause. When the fourth year came, the @@yfirst act@@N of the Neon
Covenant was not to establish government but to @@ylimit@@N it. Every
emergency power given an expiration. The Five Seats designed with
@@ymutual check@@N against indefinite authority.

Shadowmere did not do this. The @@rPlague Mandate@@N authorized rapid
intake, forced quarantines, immediate cremation, suspension of
appeals. Temporary became permanent. No authority agreed on rollback.
Three contradictory decrees rang in one night: amnesty, lockdown,
requisition. The city calcified into mutually hostile systems.

The @@rLast Bell Crisis@@N: three bells ringing contradictory orders is
a signal network that has lost its protocol. In Kowloon, the Courier
Lantern Office maintains @@eone signal standard@@N. Competing signals
are @@rcompromise indicators@@N, not governance.

The @@dBlight Hydrology Doctrine@@N tells the environmental story.
Runoff routed through burial districts. Alchemical disposal entering
water channels. The blight is @@rinfrastructure memory@@N. The Temple
Circle recognizes this from the Ashfall: canals dug for order became
channels distributing poison. @@yInfrastructure built for order
becomes infrastructure that distributes catastrophe.@@N

Five factions invoke law, none legitimate. The Wardens of Iron read
them as @@rfive failure modes of emergency power@@N: the soldier who
cannot stop, the noble who cannot yield, the clerk who cannot feel,
the executioner who cannot rest, the survivor who cannot return.

Shadowmere is lawful systems turned predatory under emergency powers
without sunset. Orders stamped, witnessed, sealed, and @@rwrong@@N.
Kowloon lit the @@yNeon Covenant@@N in glowing ink so no sealed order
could hide in darkness. The Ashfall Vigil extinguishes all lights
for one hour -- and then @@ythe lights come back@@N. That is the
difference. In Shadowmere, the lights went out and @@dno one relit
them@@N.
